<@U016WQPK6J0> thanks for the introduction to GG after talking I got thinking perhaps you and <@U0172BR9Q8H> should connect over how your ideas mechanically work, I believe there might be some synergies in terms of the underlying behaviour.

If both apps built on the same idea of a programmable pool, and the contracts were designed where they pointed to an external logic contract that handled milestone management.

<@U0172BR9Q8H> you could build CommitPool with rules to verify your rides, and <@U016WQPK6J0> GG could program the segments into the milestone management contract to control who gets flagged as a valid payout participant.

This protocol could be designed like Balancer Pools where anyone can create a pool, during creation you specify the behaviour enforcer for the pool.

Governance of this is something to consider and how it work work. Is there a way that this captures enough value it warrants Governance? or would it be more pure and uniswap like.

Great chatting with you both today.
